# Posting Queue Schema

This document defines the required structure for the Google Sheets tab named **Posting Queue** used by the Medical Spa Social Media Automation workflow.

Each row represents a single social media post to be published.

---

## Required Columns

| Column Name | Type | Description |
|------------|------|-------------|
| row_number | Number | Unique row identifier used by the workflow when updating the sheet |
| Status | Text | Current processing state of the row |
| Media URL | Text | Google Drive share link to the image or video |
| Title | Text | Optional internal reference title |
| Caption | Text | Caption text for the social post |
| Platforms | Text | Optional comma-separated list of target platforms |
| Posted At | Text | Timestamp written when the post is successfully published |
| Error Message | Text | Error details written if posting fails |
| Approved By | Text | Optional reviewer or approver name |

---

## Status Values

The **Status** column supports the following values:

- **Pending**  
  Used for items waiting to be posted.

- **Posted**  
  Set automatically by the workflow after a successful post.

- **Errored**  
  Set automatically by the workflow if posting fails.

---

## Processing Rules

- Only rows with `Status = Pending` are eligible for posting.
- The workflow processes one row per scheduled run.
- After a successful post:
  - `Status` is updated to **Posted**
  - `Posted At` is populated with a timestamp
- If an error occurs:
  - `Status` is updated to **Errored**
  - `Error Message` is populated with failure details

---

## Notes

- Google Drive links must be accessible to the workflow account.
- Media type must meet platform requirements (image or video).
- This sheet acts as the system of record for posting history.
